** Potential BUG with child themes**

It would appear that the `{% include %}` is always pulling from the parent theme regardless as to whether or not the file being included is being overwritten in the child theme

My parent theme has an overrides.css file whose contents are:
```
{% include './user/_user-overrides.css' %}
/* --------------------- */
/* Theme overrides Start */
/* --------------------- */
{% include './user/theme-overrides.css' %}```
My child theme has a new _user-overrides.css file at the same relative path yet the theme pulls the original one in the parent.

It appears that I can fix this by simply writing a new overrides.css file in the child theme with the same content as above.

Is this intended functionality?
